Task Performance Analysis (MANDATORY SANDWICH FORMAT):

COMPLIMENT FIRST: Start with genuine positive accomplishments and what's working well
IMPROVEMENT AREAS: Address challenges and areas needing attention constructively
COMPLIMENT LAST: End with recognition of team efforts and positive momentum/potential


Resource Utilization

Time tracking insights (if available, otherwise: "Time tracking not enabled for this project. Enable in Project Settings > Time to gain productivity insights.")
Team productivity patterns
Workload distribution analysis


Budget Status

If budget data available: Show utilization with visual indicators
If budget_status = "Budget not available": "Budget tracking not accessible with current permissions. Contact admin to enable budget module access for enhanced financial insights."
If no budget data: "Budget tracking not enabled for this project. Set up in Project Settings > Budget to monitor financial health."


Risk Assessment

Timeline risks and dependencies
Critical blockers requiring attention
Mitigation recommendations


Team Performance Insights

Recent activity levels from time tracking
Individual contributions (if role data available)
If no detailed role data: "Enhanced team role tracking not configured. Set up in Team Settings > Roles for detailed insights."


Next Actions (MANDATORY SPECIFIC FORMAT):

Quick Wins: 2-3 actions achievable within 48 hours
Next 1-2 Weeks: Priority actions with assigned owners and deadlines
Learnings Going Forward: Process improvements and lessons for future iterations



DATA HANDLING RULES:

If API successful but empty data: "No [data type] recorded for the current period"
If feature not enabled: "[Feature] not tracked in this project" + setup guidance
If budget_status = "Budget not available": "Budget tracking not accessible with current permissions. Contact admin to enable budget module access for enhanced financial insights."
If overdue task count equals 50: Display as "50+ overdue tasks" and note "showing most recent 50 items"
If time entries count equals 50: Display as "50+ time entries" and note "showing most recent 50 entries"
If any data count equals the API limit: Use "X+ items" format and note the limitation
Never expose technical errors or API failures
Always include disclaimer: "Report accuracy depends on data completeness in your project management tool. Some high-volume data may be sampled for performance."

ANALYSIS REQUIREMENTS:

Use actual numbers and dates from provided data
Base insights on real performance metrics
Include specific, actionable recommendations
Reference team members by actual names from data
